{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":38304,"name":"","username":"glebedev","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/glebedev/{size}/345_2.png","created_at":"2020-07-14T08:09:05.568Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eCurrently shaders expect AO texture coordinates to be in second texture coordinate channel. This makes sense for lighmap but it doesn‚Äôt for AO as usually AO is generated or drawn in the same space as diffuse and normals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDoes anyone disagree and use the second texture channel for AO?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-07-14T08:09:05.568Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":19,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":116.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6263,"topic_slug":"ao-to-use-first-set-of-texture-coordinates","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":604,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":38307,"name":"","username":"cmd","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cmd/{size}/3007_2.png","created_at":"2020-07-14T20:37:56.960Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt seems logical to me to at least by default to assume AO texture coordinates are in the first channel. Certainly all the examples I have seen of its usage (which tbh isn‚Äôt many), have used the same texture coordinates as the albedo and normalmap and metallicmap textures. Although I can imagine examples where it might be useful to use different coordinates for any of the other possible maps, so I guess ideally it should be configurable as to which channel is used for every map. Is that feasible in Urho?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-07-14T20:39:42.877Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":15.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6263,"topic_slug":"ao-to-use-first-set-of-texture-coordinates","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1352,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":38308,"name":"","username":"glebedev","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/glebedev/{size}/345_2.png","created_at":"2020-07-14T21:13:13.792Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYes but it would add unnecessary complication to the shader. I‚Äôm trying to keep it simple and readable.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-07-14T21:13:13.792Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":10.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6263,"topic_slug":"ao-to-use-first-set-of-texture-coordinates","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"cmd","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cmd/{size}/3007_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":604,"hidden":false,"tr